{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_30","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final`.\n\nPreserved work branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-818-fails-java-run-org.hibernate-hibernate-core-6.1.0.Final-30783e85\n\nMost likely failure sequence:\n- The original `fails-java-run` failure is a real JVM test failure in `OracleDialectHibernateTest`: Hibernate 6.1.0.Final initializes `OracleArrayJdbcType`, which tries to load `oracle.jdbc.OracleConnection`, and the test run fails with `ClassNotFoundException: oracle.jdbc.OracleConnection`. See `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T07-33-56-661220Z.log`.\n- The preserved work branch contains a candidate fix adding `com.oracle.database.jdbc:ojdbc11:23.2.0.0` to `tests/src/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/6.1.0.Final/build.gradle`; the rationale and diff are recorded in `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/fix-java-run-fail/pi-generation-2026-05-03T07-35-17-139975Z.log`.\n- After that candidate fix, the workflow appears to get past the original Oracle JDBC classpath problem, but it still fails in the native validation lane: `:nativeTest` reports `MissingReflectionRegistrationError` for `org.hibernate.dialect.H2Dialect`, `StrategySelectionException`/`NoSuchMethodException` for `org.hibernate.dialect.SQLServerDialect`, and `OracleDialectHibernateTest` fails with `Could not interpret id generator strategy [org.hibernate.id.enhanced.TableGenerator]`. See `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-05-03T07-35-17-147693Z.log` and `build/tests/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/41f4ec5b980eafff5dccd464311141f1.out`.\n- Native trace verification also surfaces a missing resource registration for `META-INF/services/org.junit.platform.launcher.PostDiscoveryFilter`; see `human-intervention-logs/org.hibernate:hibernate-core:6.1.0.Final/native-test-verify/cycle-0-runNativeTraceImage-2026-05-03T07-36-13-040719Z.log`.\n- Metrics show the automation did not finish a successful repair/finalization: `stats/org.hibernate/hibernate-core/6.1.0.Final/execution-metrics.json` records `status: failure`, `iterations: 1`, `generated_loc: 0`, and the same starting/ending commit `f5339f87a3aa25f82a18de7b92533cd34b063416`.\n\nManual next steps:\n1. Review/cherry-pick the preserved branch change adding `ojdbc11` and rerun the targeted JVM test lane to confirm the original `oracle.jdbc.OracleConnection` failure is resolved.\n2. Investigate the native regressions separately, especially the inactive H2 reflection metadata condition (`typeReached: org.h2.Driver`), SQLServer dialect instantiation, and the Oracle `TableGenerator` mapping failure.\n3. If the JVM fix is sufficient for this issue, land that minimal fix first and file a separate follow-up for the native-image metadata/test failures using the logs above."}}
